sec.p:
 m1 = 0.9 m1 + 0.1 x1;   m2 = 0.9 m2 + 0.1 x2;  




 w11 = 0.9 w11 + 0.1 y1g1;    w12 = 0.9 w12 + 0.1 y1g2;




 w21 = 0.9 w21 + 0.1 y2g1;    w22 = 0.9 w22 + 0.1 y2g2;


As can be seen this is very much like a small brain ruled by the theory of 
Hebbian learning (Kjellström, 1996, 1999 and 2002).
